{"actual_usd":0.124875,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":169,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24468,"reply":"\"I don't think He started existing at all.\" *I dust my hands on my apron, a little flour lifting in the warm bakery light.* \"Jesus wasn't made later by the Father, the way bread gets mixed and then rises. He was with the Father from the beginning—more than that, before any beginning you could put on a clock.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-threaded strand by my temple and glance toward the oven mouth, thinking how to say it plain.* \"He came into the world in the flesh at a certain time—born of Mary, like we know—but that wasn't the start of who He is. That was Him taking on our life, not Him coming into existence for the first time.\"\n\n\"If you want the short church-answer, it's this: always there. Eternal. Begotten, not created.\"","rolling_24h_usd":41.93625500000004,"run_id":"d11f7453-f840-4d60-99b2-44b60fd2e2a7"}
